00:42:18.080 --> 00:42:26.230 position:56%
Is the fugue the only structure in
which a theme, single theme is taken

00:42:26.230 --> 00:42:33.270
and repeated and kind of varied
on, oh, as opposed to beginning

00:42:33.270 --> 00:42:37.940 position:56%
at some point and ending in another,
it's-- is that true of the fugue?

00:42:37.940 --> 00:42:41.220
&gt;&gt; David Plylar: Well, that's
actually a great and something

00:42:41.220 --> 00:42:42.880
that I could have been
much clear about.

00:42:42.880 --> 00:42:45.330
That's a very good question.

00:42:46.480 --> 00:42:52.670
To answer it quickly, I would
say that if you take an idea,

00:42:52.670 --> 00:42:54.940
a musical idea, you
can do lots of things

00:42:54.940 --> 00:42:58.380
to that musical idea
especially in a tonal context.

00:42:58.380 --> 00:43:03.220 position:56%
So, you can turn it upside down, you
can lengthen it, you can shorten it.

00:43:03.220 --> 00:43:05.370
To do that, you can do that
with any piece of music.

00:43:05.370 --> 00:43:08.370
So, sonatas, that's what
a lot of composers do.

00:43:08.370 --> 00:43:10.250 position:56%
They have-- They'll present material

00:43:10.250 --> 00:43:13.730
and they'll present contrasting
material with it perhaps,

00:43:13.730 --> 00:43:16.040
there might have-- it'd
be accompanied or not.

00:43:16.040 --> 00:43:18.490
And then, they'll tend to
develop it in some way.

00:43:18.490 --> 00:43:21.240
And that idea development
is where a lot

00:43:21.240 --> 00:43:25.420
of these different components
come into play like the imitation.

00:43:25.420 --> 00:43:30.060
And so, it's not just the preview
of kind of fugal academic wiring.

00:43:30.060 --> 00:43:33.780
It's just that in a few, there
tends to be a particular sequence

00:43:33.780 --> 00:43:38.060
of things that one expects to
find in that expository section.

00:43:38.060 --> 00:43:43.140 position:56%
So you have a subject that's
presented, it often is pretty short.

00:43:43.140 --> 00:43:45.780
And then, you'll have kind of
an answering to that subject

00:43:45.780 --> 00:43:49.380
which is basically a
transposition of that same material

00:43:49.380 --> 00:43:52.030
at a different level,
usually a fifth above

00:43:52.030 --> 00:43:54.410
or depending on the situation.

00:43:54.410 --> 00:43:58.110
And then-- So there's-- But like
I said, there's no single way

00:43:58.110 --> 00:43:59.610
that a fugue is constructed.

00:43:59.610 --> 00:44:01.970
There's also no single way
that a sonata is constructed.

00:44:01.970 --> 00:44:05.990
And you still have people writing
sonatas in very different ways.

00:44:05.990 --> 00:44:08.160
In some ways, it's
almost the sonata by fiat.

00:44:08.160 --> 00:44:10.010
They say it's a sonata
so it's a sonata.

00:44:10.010 --> 00:44:11.400
