There's one up here.

00:45:49.120 --> 00:45:53.810
&gt;&gt; It seems to me a few years
ago at the Freer Gallery,

00:45:53.810 --> 00:45:57.820
I remember hearing the Brahms,
but it was two-pianists,

00:45:57.820 --> 00:46:01.000
it was Emanuel Ax and a woman--

00:46:01.000 --> 00:46:02.300
&gt;&gt; David Plylar: Maybe--

00:46:02.300 --> 00:46:04.140
&gt;&gt; And I'm wondering, did the
Brahms recasts this several times?

00:46:04.140 --> 00:46:05.720
&gt;&gt; David Plylar: I think
in the Haydn variations.

00:46:05.720 --> 00:46:07.020
&gt;&gt; Oh. OK.

00:46:07.020 --> 00:46:09.560 position:56%
&gt;&gt; David Plylar: No, no, because he
